  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN195.1-kilavi">makaṭpōkkiya naṟṟāy colliyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What the real mother said who had let [her] daughter go.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN195.1">
        <l><anchor n="1"/>aruñcura miṟantaveṉ peruntōṭ kuṟumaka</l>
        <l>ṭiruntuvēl viṭalaiyoṭu varumeṉat tāyē</l>
        <l>puṉaimā ṇiñci pūva lūṭṭi</l>
        <l>maṉaimaṇa laṭuttu mālai nāṟṟi</l>
        <l>yuvantiṉi tayaru meṉpa yāṉu</l>
        <l>māṉpiṇai nōkkiṉ maṭanal lāḷai</l>
        <l>yīṉṟa naṭpiṟ karuḷā ṉāyiṉu</l>
        <l>miṉṉakai muṟuva lēḻaiyaip paṉṉāṭ<anchor n="2"/></l>
        <l>kūntal vāri nucuppivarn tōmpiya</l>
        <l>nalampuṉai yutaviyu<anchor n="3"/> muṭaiyaṉ maṉ<supplied>ṉō</supplied></l>
        <l>vaḵtaṟi kaṟpi ṉaṉṟumaṟ ṟilla</l>
        <l>vaṟuvai tōyu moruperuṅ kuṭumic</l>
        <l>ciṟupai<anchor n="4"/> nāṟṟiya paḵṟalaik koṭuṅkō</l>
        <l>lākuva taṟiyu mutuvāy vēla</l>
        <l>kūṟuka mātōniṉ kaḻaṅkiṉ ṟiṭpa</l>
        <l>māṟā varumpaṉi kaluḻuṅ kaṅkuli</l>
        <l>lāṉātu tuyarumeṅ kaṇṇiṉitu paṭīiya</l>
        <l>remmaṉai muntuṟat tarumō</l>
        <l>taṉmaṉai yuykkumō<anchor n="5"/> yātavaṉ kuṟippē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>“Thinking ‘my little daughter with wide shoulders, who has gone to traverse</l>
        <l>the difficult desert, will come [back] along with a warrior with a perfect spear’, her mother, (1f.)</l>
        <l>she feeds red earth to the gloriously decorated ramparts, (3)</l>
        <l>puts sand in the house, suspends garlands (4)</l>
        <l>[and] joyously prepares for something pleasant”, they say, and as for myself, (5)</l>
        <l>even though he is not considerate with respect to the connection that has brought forth (7)</l>
        <l>the innocent good girl with the glance of a doe, (6)</l>
        <l>will I too really have a hand in combing the tresses</l>
        <l>of the foolish girl with a sweet smile, many days,</l>
        <l>[and] decorating [her] with a good [ornament] that moves around [and] protects [her] waist? (7-10)</l>
        <l>If one could learn that so as to know it, that would be good indeed. (11)</l>
        <l>With one big [hair] tuft touched by [his] garment, (12)</l>
        <l>with a curved staff with many knobs from which are suspended little bags, (13)</l>
        <l>oh spear bearer with ancient truth who knows what will happen, (14)</l>
        <l>won’t you tell [me] of the certainty [revealed] by your molucca beans? (15)</l>
        <l>In the night that dims with dew that comes without change, (16)</l>
        <l>let my eyes that grieve without end close sweetly. (17)</l>
        <l>Will he first bring [her] to our house? (18)</l>
        <l>Will he sent [her] to his own house? What is his intention? (19)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>

